Document: MeshDataTool
Path: godot/tutorials/3d/procedural_geometry/meshdatatool.rst
Summary: This document explains the MeshDataTool class in Godot, which allows for direct manipulation of mesh data like vertices, normals, and UVs.

Mesh data can be accessed and modified directly using the MeshDataTool class. This is useful for procedural geometry generation or modifying existing meshes.

Inherits: RefCounted < Object

Methods:
Method: create_from_surface(mesh: Mesh, surface_index: int) → Error
Creates a MeshDataTool from a specific surface of a Mesh. Returns an Error code.

Method: get_vertex_count() → int
Returns the number of vertices in the mesh.

Method: get_vertex(vertex_index: int) → Vector3
Returns the position of a vertex.

Method: set_vertex(vertex_index: int, vertex: Vector3)
Sets the position of a vertex.

Method: get_normal_count() → int
Returns the number of normals in the mesh.

Method: get_normal(vertex_index: int) → Vector3
Returns the normal of a vertex.

Method: set_normal(vertex_index: int, normal: Vector3)
Sets the normal of a vertex.

Method: get_uv_count() → int
Returns the number of UV layers in the mesh.

